(234, 1, '2024-03-20 13:57:29', '2024-03-20 13:57:29', 'Tom Beck thrives in the uncommon space between. Between engineering and design; between constant motion and careful consideration; between the impossibly taxing and the insanely relaxing. Tom excels equally on both ends of a unique duality and at every point in between. As the Chief Technical Officer of Ocupop, Tom has led the firmâ€™s tight team of designers, developers and strategists to create revolutionary user experiences, applications, and brand activations for clients large and small.\r\n\r\nFrom Google and Mozilla to IRC, Sustainable America, and the Mott Foundation, Tom connects the inspiration and energy of Ocupopâ€™s category-defining designs with its groundbreaking engineering output. Just as comfortable defining data models as he is in debating design details, Tomâ€™s unique perspective and unending enthusiasm for getting shit done makes every Ocupop employee, client and colleague more productive, more successful, and just plain happier to be alive.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Ocupop, Tom received his BS from University of Colorado, Boulder before working extensively for Merrill Lynch on global event concepting and production.Â  Equally at home in the mountains of British Columbia as in the barrel at Honolua Bay, the Beckâ€™s (Tom, Nicole, Evan and Leila) stay on the move, splitting time between Whistler and Maui, making sure to make the most of both extremesâ€¦and each and every minute in between.', 'Tom Beck', 'Chief Technical Officer', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'tom-beck', '', '', '2024-04-02 20:36:50', '2024-04-02 20:36:50', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8001/?post_type=team&#038;p=234', 0, 'team', '', 0),
